Italian politics, and his writing commanded attention throughout Europe, America, and beyond. In the last few years his contribution to various disciplines has been undergoing a re-evaluation in Italy. This collection continues that reassessment with an English-speaking audience in mind.The book is a collection of essays by scholars from various disciplines - philosophy, history, literature, and art history - covering the broad scope of Croce's life and work, from his early writings on local Neopolitan history in the 1890s to his activity as a public figure before and after the Second World War. In this much-needed addition to contemporary criticism one senses the depth and originality of his thought in the areas of history, national politics, rhetoric, and art. Including the first English-language discussion of Taccuini di lavoro, Croce's working diary, this is the first volume in English that provides a critical survey of Croce's major works and ideas, as well as fresh interpretations from a variety of contemporary points of view.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aCavaliere, Renata Viti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD\x27amico, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinocchiaro, Maurice A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobitti, Edmund E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMazzotta, Giuseppe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMelillo, Rita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoss, Myra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoberts, David D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrafton, Dain A., eauthor.4aut4